description: Valorie Pony Teter  shared  Radio One Lebanon 's  photo  — with  Corinne Cullinan . Lol Radio One Lebanon Robert Young

I gave myself a few days to relax and attempt to acclimate to normal life, but I'm realizing that "normal" is a relative term when put into the context of newlywed life. We have a LOT of thank yous to put into cards and phone calls and visits, but there are some standouts that I want to publicly praise. Bear with me here...     I'll start with my VIPs: Thanks to John C for putting in eight months o ... f hard labor coordinating input and opinions and one-off suggestions from half a dozen people and wrangling a dozen vendors -- all with total poise and graciousness, as usual, to the point that I believe Kingwood is preparing a job offer for you. Without you this *literally* couldn't have happened. (And also thanks for being my dance partner for Shake It Off!) Thanks to  Sophia  for taking the flowers and plants and decorations to such a supreme level of gorgeousness I never imagined possible -- you really set a new standard for beauty, and you made it somehow look effortless! And also THANK YOU thank you for keeping me grounded & human throughout the whole crazy frantic process (I know that that was truly no small feat). And thanks thanks a billion times thanks to the incredible, inimitable  Alexandra  for not only throwing all of her time, energy and money into making me look and feel as beautiful as humanly possible, but for forgoing all sleep, sanity and sustenance in the 48-72 hours before the event -- and for at least another 24 hours after -- in order to perform some honest-to-god miracles in the coordination and decoration details. I don't know how on earth the three of you were able to do the things you did, much less survive the whole ordeal, but I am completely awestruck.     Thank you also to my crew of good-looking girlfriends for collectively making me look great by association. To  Cher-Wen  for being such a behind-the-scenes star, knowing what I needed done without me having to ask (instead just throwing you panicked looks) -- and to  Eric  for being such a hero and driving all the way to Oberlin for Agave nachos. To  Lilly  for proving herself to be a pro-cat herder by somehow getting my family to miraculously quiet down when needed, and for making me get my hair done even though I kept saying I didn't need to (I did). To  Lydia  &  Marjorie , my favorite duo, for always showing up for me and looking glamorous while doing so for over a decade now. You two are unstoppable.     THANK YOU to  Stewart  for officiating the classiest, most entertaining and heartwarming wedding ceremony in modern history. You managed to put two introverts at total ease in front of a crowd, which is nothing short of a miracle in my book. And to  Courtney  for being *literally* the loveliest human being I have ever met. (And to Scout for loaning the two of them to us for the weekend)     Thank you to  Guiding Light Music/Film  for creating the perfect DJ set, without which we might never have got half the Marvars on the dance floor. (sorrynotsorry for making you play Taylor Dayne)     Thank you to  Benjamin  for being so completely and utterly and unexpectedly integral to the weekend's events, I don't even know how to properly thank you for showing up other than to just say thank you a thousand times.     And last but not even close to least, thank you to all of our friends and family who came, who danced, who sang Mnohaya Lita, who did shots of Slivovitz with my dad, who drove pierogies in from Cleveland, who made it exactly what we hoped it would be -- THANK YOU. The whole day was a blur of hugs and kisses and well wishes from all of the people nearest and dearest to us, and I'm still glowing from it all.  <3   <3   <3   See More
